<title>USA: Hybridon to sell $50 mln in notes.</title>
<headline>Hybridon to sell $50 mln in notes.</headline>
<dateline>CAMBRIDGE, Mass 1997-03-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hybridon Inc said Thursday it agreed to sell its $50 million convertible subordinated notes due 2004.</p>
<p>The closing is expected to occur on April 2 and is subject to satisfaction of certain conditions. The notes will be convertible into common shares at $7.0125 a share.</p>
<p>Hybridon is a biopharmaceutical company based here.</p>
